One man sustained critical burns to most of his body, while a woman was moderately injured. JOHANNESBURG - Two people have been injured in an explosion at Southgate Mall. It's understood a transformer exploded earlier today but it's not yet clear what caused it to explode. One man sustained critical burns to most of his body, while a woman was moderately injured. ER24's Russel Meiring said, &quot;Paramedics treated both patients and provided them with numerous advanced life support interventions. Once treated, they were transported to a private hospital in Johannesburg for urgent care. Local authorities will be investigating the cause of this incident.&quot;